definitions.definition: To vibrate or sound , especially in response to another vibration.
examples: The books on top of the piano resonate when he plays certain notes.

definitions.definition: To have an effect or impact ; to influence ; to engender support .
examples: His words resonated with the crowd.

definitions.definition: To agree or sympathise, not necessarily perfectly, usually with an emotion, an attitude, or an intellectual position.

main_definition: To vibrate or sound , especially in response to another vibration.
